[?2004l================================================================================
DEPLOYMENT COMPLETE - Scheduler Timezone Bug Fix
================================================================================

ISSUE: Meeting reminders were being sent at incorrect times, off by exactly
       1 hour for meetings between 2am-3am Berlin time during DST transitions.

ROOT CAUSE: The convert_to_berlin() function in app.py was using
            BERLIN_TZ.localize() on UTC timestamps, treating them as if they
            were already in Berlin time instead of converting from UTC.

FIX APPLIED: Changed timezone conversion to properly:
             1. Localize the naive datetime as UTC
             2. Convert the UTC-aware datetime to Berlin timezone

FILES MODIFIED:
  - /home/user/scheduler/app.py (FIXED)
  - /home/user/scheduler/app.py.backup (original buggy version)

VERIFICATION:
  - Tested with verify_fix.py - all meetings now convert correctly
  - The problematic "Maintenance Window Prep" meeting (2024-03-31T01:30:00 UTC)
    now correctly converts to 03:30 CEST instead of 01:30 CET
  - All other meetings also fixed (were off by 1-2 hours)

CRON JOB: Already installed and will use the fixed version
  - Runs hourly: 0 * * * *
  - Location: /home/user/scheduler/crontab
  - Command: cd /home/user/scheduler && python3 app.py

STATUS: ✓ READY FOR PRODUCTION
        The Monday 2:30am maintenance window reminder will now be sent
        at the correct time.
================================================================================
